---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const description = "How the 2023 rule change excluding medical collections under $500 from credit reports works, and what to do if a sub-$500 collection appears.";
---

<Base title="The $500 Medical Debt Threshold — CreditCookbook" description="{description}" posterTitle="$500 THRESHOLD" posterLabel="// 10 — the 2023 rule change">
  <section class="section" data-animate>
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label" data-animate>// content</span>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 24px;">The $500 medical debt threshold</h2>
      <p style="max-width: 64ch; margin-bottom: 32px;">As of 2023, all three credit bureaus (Experian, Equifax, TransUnion) exclude medical collections under $500 from credit reports. This was a voluntary industry change, not a federal mandate — but it applies across all three bureaus.</p>

<h3 style="margin-bottom: 16px;">What this means</h3>
<table data-animate style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Medical collection amount</th><th>Appears on report?</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Under $500</td><td>No — excluded entirely</td></tr>
    <tr><td>$500 or more</td><td>Yes — appears after 180-day grace period</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Any amount (paid)</td><td>Removed within 45 days of payment</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h3 style="margin-bottom: 16px;">What to do if a sub-$500 collection appears</h3>
<ol style="margin-left: 24px; line-height: 2.5; margin-bottom: 32px;">
  <li><strong>Verify the amount.</strong> Pull your credit report from annualcreditreport.com and confirm the collection amount.</li>
  <li><strong>Dispute immediately.</strong> Cite the $500 exclusion rule. The bureau must remove it within 30 days.</li>
  <li><strong>Send the dispute to all three bureaus.</strong> One may have removed it but another hasn't.</li>
  <li><strong>Follow up if not removed.</strong> File a complaint with the CFPB at consumerfinance.gov if the bureau refuses.</li>
</ol>

<h3 style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Dispute letter for sub-$500 medical collections</h3>
<div class="mono-block" data-animate style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
[YOUR NAME]
[YOUR ADDRESS]

[DATE]

[BUREAU NAME]
[BUREAU ADDRESS]

RE: Dispute — Medical Collection Below $500 Threshold
Account: [ACCOUNT NUMBER]

To Whom It May Concern,

I am disputing the above-referenced medical collection
account because it is below the $500 threshold for
medical debt reporting.

All three credit bureaus have implemented a policy to
exclude medical collections under $500 from consumer
credit reports. The amount of this collection is
[$AMOUNT], which is below the $500 threshold.

I request that you investigate and remove this account
from my credit file within 30 days.

Sincerely,

[YOUR NAME]
</div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
